The paper deals with convolutional networks for analyzing spatio-temporal data such as images, videos, and 3D shapes. The focus is on processing spatially-sparse data more efficiently, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also involves developing models for semantic segmentation (cs.AI) of 3D point clouds, which is a subfield of computer graphics (cs.GR) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
